Crosstown Traffic (The Jimi Hendrix Experience) played before and as the band walked on stage for the second set. The Altered Beast suite and The Balrog were introduced as new songs. Before Alter Me I, the band took a moment to fix loud buzzing coming from Ambrose's equipment. Invisible Face was incomplete. Am I In Heaven? contained Alter Me and Cellophane teases and quotes, Rattlesnake, Hot Water, and Head On/Pill teases, and a Sea Of Trees jam with lyrics. KGLW.net Staff Notes: The setlist for this show is believed to be complete. Alter Me I through Am I In Heaven? were confirmed by the band's Facebook livestream. The remaining songs were confirmed through contemporaneous discussions through various social media, but any additional setlist notations that require audio confirmation (guest appearances, segues, quotes or teases) may be incomplete. If anyone has any further information or, ideally, a complete or conclusive recording please contact KGLW.net staff at setlist@kglw.net.

High Voltage (AC/DC) played before and as the band walked on stage for the first set. All Is Known was introduced as a new song and contained alternate lyrics. During Billabong Valley, the guitar strap fell off the Flying Microtonal Banana while Ambrose was using it, with Joey jokingly telling Stu afterwards that his guitar was broken and that Ambrose should "stick to the blues harp". NOBODY'S BABY (Sheer Mag) played before and as the band walked on stage for the second set. Before Gamma Knife, the crowd started chanting for Stu to do a "shoey", to which he told them to "be reasonable" and that he was "too old for that". The Balrog was introduced as a new song. Am I In Heaven? contained a medley of teases and quotes including Alter Me, Cellophane, Rattlesnake, Hot Water, Head On/Pill and The River as well as a Sea of Trees jam with lyrics. This performance was filmed in 360-degree video and released as "King Gizzard & The Lizard Wizard - 360° Full Concert" on the Banalarama YouTube channel, featuring audio mixed by Stu
Webcast live by Pitchfork. Night one was performed in the grand ballroom.

This show featured the debut of Vomit Coffin. Following Rattlesnake, the band wished a happy birthday to Eric. Am I In Heaven? contained teases and quotes of Cellophane, The River, Head On/Pill, I'm In Your Mind, Sea of Trees, Rattlesnake, and Robot Stop. Prior to the show, Stu accidentally posted a link containing demos for all of Polygondwanaland to the Facebook fan page under the name “Blinky Bill”. Although removed shortly after, someone was able to download the first two demos causing Stu to message them claiming he was a fan named Han-Tyumi and asked for the demos not to be reposted. KGLW.net Staff Notes: The setlist for this show is believed to be complete, but no recordings are available. John Peel set

This show featured the debuts of Some Context, Welcome to an Altered Future, Digital Black, and Han-Tyumi, The Confused Cyborg. Billabong Valley was dedicated to Charles Bradley, who had passed that day. Lonely Steel Sheet Flyer was played for the first time known since 2015-09-11. (174 show gap) Robot Stop contained a Master Of The Universe' jam with lyrics.

Members of Mild High Club joined the band for Countdown and Rolling Stoned. Countdown was performed without the keyboard solo as the band forgot to play it. KGLW.net Staff Notes: The setlist is believed to be complete. The Lord of Lightning, Sleep Drifter, Lonely Steel Sheet Flyer, Robot Stop, Countdown and Rolling Stoned were confirmed by audio/video recordings. The remaining songs were confirmed via contemporaneous discussions through various social media, but any additional setlist notations that require audio confirmation (guest appearances, segues, quotes or teases) may be incomplete. The first performance of Rolling Stoned was played as the last song of Mild High Club's set, with the members of King Gizzard joining in mid-song. Robot Stop contained a Master of the Universe jam with lyrics. Members of Mild High Club joined the band for Countdown and the second performance of Rolling Stoned. KGLW.net Staff Notes: The setlist is believed to be complete. The band walked out to Let There Be Rock by AC/DC.
Robot Stop contained a Master Of The Universe jam with lyrics.
Am I In Heaven? contained People Vultures, Cut Throat Boogie, Rattlesnake, Alter Me, Robot Stop, Cellophane, I'm In Your Mind, Head On/Pill, and Float Along - Fill Your Lungs teases and quotes.

This was an appearance for radio station KEXP in Seattle. The performance was held for a live audience at the KEXP Gathering Space and was hosted by KEXP DJ Cheryl Waters. Han-Tyumi, The Confused Cyborg featured Stu on flute and alternate lyrics.

Riff Raff (AC/DC) played as the band came on stage. Before Digital Black, Joey said "this is our biggest show in America, ever", and Stu thanked Amyl & The Sniffers (the opening act). Vomit Coffin was incomplete. Alter Me I was incomplete. Before Rattlesnake, Stu shouted out John Bonham as a "s--t bloke, good drummer", followed by a short Moby Dick (Led Zeppelin) tease. The vocal intro to Nuclear Fusion was not performed. Before The Wheel Joey shouted out Sammy on the sound, Jason Galea who was working the projectors, Gaspard who was working the monitors, and "Nate Dog on the merch". Robot Stop contained Hot Water teases, and the intro contained a Trapdoor tease. Joey thanked Amyl & The Sniffers again after Gamma Knife.

“Whiplash” (Metallica) played as the band came on stage. Vomit Coffin and Alter Me I were incomplete. Before Rattlesnake, Stu shouted out Amyl & The Sniffers, the opening act. Greenhouse Heat Death contained a Sleep Drifter tease. Sleep Drifter contained a Rattlesnake tease. Billabong Valley contained a Sleep Drifter tease. After The Wheel, Joey said "That song was our Jerry Garcia attempt". The intro to Robot Stop contained Trapdoor, Cellophane, and Hot Water teases, and the song itself contained a Hot Water tease. At the end of the show, Joey shouted out the Golden State Warriors, the local NBA team, who were in the midst of the 2018 NBA finals series.

Head On/Pill was played for the first time since 2017-06-24. (68 show gap). The intro to Robot Stop contained Trapdoor and Hot Water teases. Head On/Pill contained Sea of Trees teases and quotes, Hot Water teases, Alter Me I teases and quotes, Am I In Heaven? teases and quotes, a Robot Stop tease, and Cellophane teases and quotes.

The intro to Robot Stop contained Cellophane and Head On/Pill teases. KGLW.net Staff Notes: The setlist for this show is believed to be complete, but only partial recordings are available. Robot Stop through Big Fig Wasp, Rattlesnake, All Is Known through Digital Black and The Lord of Lightning through Crumbling Castle have been confirmed via audio/video recordings. The remaining songs were confirmed by contemporaneous discussions through various social media, but any additional setlist notations that require audio confirmation (guest appearances, segues, quotes or teases) may be incomplete. If anyone has any further information or, ideally, a complete or conclusive recording please contact KGLW.net staff at setlists@kglw.net.
Altered Beast II was played for the first time since 2017-10-14. (53 show gap)

Vomit Coffin was incomplete, and only one verse of Alter Me I was sung. Robot Stop contained Head On/Pill and Hot Water teases. Head On/Pill contained Alter Me quotes, Cellophane, Sea of Trees, and Am I In Heaven? teases and quotes, and Hot Water and Robot Stop teases
I'm In Your Mind was played for the first time since 2017-01-21. (133 shows) Alter Me II was played for the first time since 2017-12-02. (50 show gap)

Before Digital Black, Stu asked the crowd if anyone was at the band's previous show in Atlanta, followed by Cavs briefly teasing Moby Dick. Hot Wax, which was played for the first time known since 2016-05-14 (199 show gap), was performed at the request of a fan who asked the band after their previous show if they could play it. Billabong Valley was dedicated to "all them abandoned kitties next door". Sleep Drifter contained a Honey intro tease. After All Is Known, Joey shouted out an audience member's 21st birthday and brought them on stage. Only Part I of The River was played, and it contained a brief blues intro. Wah Wah was played for the first time since 2016-12-09 (138 show gap) and contained The River quotes and teases. Robot Stop contained a “Master Of The Universe” (Hawkwind) jam with lyrics and Hot Water teases.
Mystery Jack was played for the first time known since 2013-08-29. (415 show gap)
Alter Me III and Altered Beast IV were played for the first time since 2017-12-02. (57 show gap)
The Balrog was played for the first time since 2017-03-24. (133 show gap) I'm In Your Mind Fuzz was played for the first time since 2017-11-23. (66 show gap)

This show was broadcast live by NPO 3 Extra. “Stayin' In Black” (Bee Gees + AC/DC by Wax Audio) played through the PA as the band came on stage. Following Altered Beast II, Joey joked that he preferred Lowlands over Pukkelpop (another European festival the band played the day before). Sleep Drifter contained Billabong Valley and Rattlesnake teases. Robot Stop contained a Hot Water tease and a Master of The Universe jam with lyrics.

This show opened with an extended jam before the band's set that evolved out of the band tuning, which contained Head On/Pill teases. Am I In Heaven? was played for the first time since 2017-10-07. (81 show gap) KGLW.net Staff Notes: The setlist may be incomplete and out of order. Evil Star was played through the PA speakers as the band went on stage. Beginner's Luck was introduced as a song about Stu's gambling addiction. After Organ Farmer, Joey thanked openers Stonefield and ORB. Am I In Heaven? contained Mars For The Rich and Venusian 2 teases and Alter Me, Boogieman Sam and Hot Water teases and quotes KGLW.net Staff Notes: The setlist is believed to be complete. Evil Star was played through the PA speakers before and as the band went on stage. Alter Me I contained Evil Death Roll teases. The Bitter Boogie contained Cut Throat Boogie and On The Road Again (Canned Heat) quotes. ‘Inner Cell’, ‘Loyalty’, and ‘Horology’ from this show are featured in the ‘Chunky Shrapnel’ album.

Poster By Jason Galea
Edition of 400

This show featured the live debut of A New World. Slow Jam 1 contained Ice V and Flamethrower teases, as well as Iron Lung quotes. The Grim Reaper featured an additional verse from Sadie Sorceress played over the music to The Grim Reaper followed by Sadie Sorceress quotes and teases. Ice V contained Slow Jam 1 quotes. A New World through Altered Beast II featured narration by Leah Senior. Altered Beast I was played for the first time since 2022-10-05 (90 show gap). Alter Me I and Altered Beast II were played for the first time since 2019-10-06 (87 show gap). Work This Time featured a guitar solo. Leah Senior was shouted out after Magma. The Dripping Tap contained Hypertension quotes and Hell’s Itch and Head On/Pill teases.

Poster by Jason Galea
320 Standard / 40 Foil Print

Stu and Ambrose wished Joey a happy birthday during The Dripping Tap. Gaia featured a Cavs drum solo over a metal vamp from the band. Oddlife was introduced as “Cookie’s favorite song”. Boogieman Sam was dedicated to soundman Sam Joseph and contained Cut Throat Boogie teases/quotes, “My Babe” (Little Walter), “Got My Mojo Working” (Ann Cole), and “Going Up the Country” (Canned Heat) quotes and Sleepwalker teases. Sea of Trees was introduced as “what King Gizzard was originally called” and “Lucas’s favorite song”, and contained Head On/Pill and The Bitter Boogie teases. Hypertension was played over the PA as the setbreak music, which incidentally served as the “debut” for the studio track. I’m Not in Your Mind contained Alter Me teases. A New World through Altered Beast III featured Leah Senior providing narration. Alter Me I contained an Altered Beast III tease. Alter Me II and Altered Beast III were played for the first time since 2019-10-07 (90 show gap). The intro to Iron Lung featured additional vocals about “hot buns”. Robot Stop contained a Hot Water tease. Iron Lung was reprised during Mr. Beat. Joey was hit with silly string at the conclusion of the show, and Ambrose quoted “Happy Birthday, Lisa” (The Simpsons) for the second night in a row. This show was released through the Official Bootlegger program as part of Live at Red Rocks ‘22. Poster By Jason Galea

Hot Wax was announced as a dedication to Joe Santarpia, one of the band's sound engineers. Hot Wax was played for the first time since 2022-04-28 (50 show gap). I’m Not in Your Mind contained Alter Me teases and quotes. Cellophane contained Am I in Heaven? teases and Hot Wax quotes. Ambergris was introduced as a song about “the most expensive ingredient in modern humanity.” Iron Lung featured an extended Red Hot Chili Peppers style intro while Lucas was using the restroom, followed by additional mid-song banter about Lucas. A New World through Altered Beast II featured Leah Senior providing the narration.

Evil Death Roll was introduced as a song about crocodiles and contained The Dripping Tap and Trapdoor teases.  Alter Me I contained Ice V teases.  Billabong Valley and Honey contained Sleep Drifter teases.  Ambrose quoted Polygondwanaland before Inner Cell. The Grim Reaper contained Torture Chamber quotes and an extra verse from Sadie Sorceress.  Los Bitchos joined the band for Trapdoor, which contained a percussion solo.

Poster by Lewy Jones

Stu and Joey wore overalls, which were also worn in the video for The Silver Cord. I’m Not In Your Mind contained Alter Me quotes and The Dripping Tap teases/quotes. Sense contained a Slow Jam 1 intro, after which Stu introduced Joey as John Frusciante and the band played a brief Red Hot Chili Peppers style jam. Sense proper contained Slow Jam 1 quotes and closed with quotes of “Incredible” (M Beat) and “Welcome to the Jungle” (Guns N’ Roses). The Grim Reaper contained Torture Chamber quotes and “Intergalactic” (Beastie Boys) quotes. Shanghai featured the “grow wings and fly” jam. Ambergris was introduced as a song about Free Willy. Hot Water had lyrics changed to “Joe Walker" and "Joey Walker." Robot Stop was unfinished and contained Hot Water teases, The Dripping Tap teases and Witchcraft teases/quotes. Lava and Gamma Knife were on the printed setlist but were not played. At the end of the show, the band thanked the crowd for coming to see the "fishermen from Australia". KGLW.net Staff Notes: There was much internal discussion as to a potential tease of the intro to Gondii in Change. The arrangement of instruments and structure of Change has been modified compared with the studio version. Though it resembles a tease of Gondii, we believe more live instances need to he heard to determine if this is intentional, or just an accentuation of the existing relationship between the songs. Poster By Jason Galea 420 Standard / 120 Foil

This was King Gizzard's first show in South America. Head On/Pill contained Robot Stop teases and Am I In Heaven? teases & quotes.  Robot Stop contained Hot Water teases & quotes.  Venusian 2 contained Converge quotes.

data.jamchart_notes: Unusually long version with a medley of teases
data.shownotes: This show featured the first full performance of Motor Spirit. Rattlesnake was introduced as a song about snakes and contained Honey and Doom City teases. Honey contained a Sleep Drifter jam. Open Water featured a drum solo by Cavs. Ice V contained Hog Calling Contest teases. Cut Throat Boogie contained Sad Pilot teases and Rats In The Sky, Raw Feel, Field of Vision and Daily Blues quotes. Most Of What I Like contained a “Praise You” (Fatboy Slim) jam with Flight b741 teases. Following Most Of What I Like, Stu teased “Sweet Home Alabama” (Lynyrd Skynyrd). The Lord of Lightning was introduced as a song about shots by Stu, and about when Stu got struck by lightning by Ambrose, and contained Cut Throat Boogie and I'm In Your Mind teases. The Alter Me I Jam contained a Hypertension jam with lyrics and Witchcraft and Cellophane teases. I'm Not In Your Mind contained Robot Stop teases. Cellophane was also introduced as a song about shots by Stu and contained Motor Spirit quotes. Joey shouted out opener Grace Cummings after I'm In Your Mind Fuzz. Dragon was introduced as a song about dragons. Poster by Amy Jean; Edition of 100

Altered Beast I was played for the first time since 2023-06-16 (96 shows), Alter Me I was played for the first time since 2024-05-18 (64 shows), and Altered Beast II was played for the first time since 2024-03-14 (72 shows). Raw Feel contained Am I In Heaven? and Head On/Pill teases. Boogieman Sam featured a guitar/harmonica duel between Joey & Amby and contained teases of Sad Pilot & The Bitter Boogie, a Mirage City jam, Altered Beast II teases and Phantom Island quotes. Chang'e was unfinished. After Hell, Joey introduced the rest of the band, followed by Stu introducing Joey. The audience then chanted "free free Palestine!"; the band encouraged them to "say that shit louder!".
data.soundcheck: Altered Beast Suite, Venusian 1, Predator X, Mirage City

data.shownotes: Altered Beast I contained an Alter Me intro.  Alter Me II was played for the first time since 2022-10-31 (177 shows) and contained Hypertension quotes and teases and Forty Six & 2 (Tool) teases. Altered Beast IV contained Hypertension teases.  Hypertension contained Riff Raff (AC/DC), Forty Six & 2 (Tool) and Sad Pilot teases. Muddy Water and The Bitter Boogie were performed as a mashup with parts of each song interspersed throughout the other.  Sad Pilot contained teases of The Bitter Boogie and Machine Gun (Jimi Hendrix).  The band's guitar tech Gaspard, introduced as Gary, played drums on Le Risque while Cavs performed his verse from the front of the stage and stayed on drums for the rest of the song.  Motor Spirit was introduced as a song about cars.  Ambrose quoted The Next Episode (Dr. Dre & Snoop Dogg) in Motor Spirit after the band took shots following Gila Monster. At the end of the show the band shouted out opener Barkaa and Joey said "from the river to the sea, free Palestine."  The written setlist had Raw Feel listed as Raw Phil, Muddy Water and The Bitter Boogie listed as Muddy Boogie // Bitter Water, Sad Pilot listed as Rad Pilot and Hot Wax listed as Hot Phacts.
